I’m a regular at Brickside I go maybe once a week. The drinks are always reasonable and my food is usually pretty good. My complaint is the customer service. Last night we had to have another waitress take over our seats because he stopped by to say hello and was never seen again. By never seen again I mean he stood still doing literally nothing for the duration of our stay. This guy wears glasses has curly hair and sometimes has a headband on. I’m not sure if he’s related to ownership since he’s worked there this long, but I can’t return to sit down there just because he still works there. He has curly hair and wears a head band so if you ever have him please ask for different server. We had 5 people sitting at our table one night when we went there so that was not much to handle. This guy got our individual checks wrong 5 times!!!! By the third time my friends girlfriend wrote all our orders down (which was a beer and food) and this guy still came back with the wrong checks.... I'm like bro you gotta be kidding me. Another waiter or waitress had to help him because he was clearly incapable of doing his job. Came back again and this guy is still working there. This dude actually needs to go. He's terrible at his job. Sorry but no sorry.

Came here for a lunch, around 1pm, and along with one other table it was just my friend and I! The waitress was AMAZING. She gave us great recommendations and told us what was good and what was not so good. If you come before 3, you’re able to get everything at happy hour price, so about $10 for entree with side. The food was amazing. Try the ranch chicken sandwich no doubt! We tried their new dessert, which was deep fried Oreos. When we first heard this, we immediately thought carnival style which turned our stomachs. But, these things are to die for! They add powdered sugar and just a little chocolate syrup which makes for the perfect small dessert after a lunch portioned meal. Great atmosphere, staff, food, and there’s street parking as well! If you’re looking for a quick and relatively cheap ($28 for two people) meal, brickside is a must!

The good: The service was great and the seating by the window is perfect for a sunny weekend morning. Pricing is reasonable as well.  The bad: I had fried chicken Benedict and fried pickles and my friend had old bay chicken wings and a Pepsi. Everything had something wrong. The Pepsi was flat. The old bay chicken wings were so dry she only ate two. My fried chicken was so dry that I couldn’t cut through it. The biscuit crumbled when I tried to cut it and there wasn’t enough gravy to coat over the fact that the biscuit tasted like cardboard. The fried pickles were okay but the pickles below the top 5 were greasy and soggy and fell apart as soon as you touched them. Neither of us are more than 4 bites and no one asked about the food or quality.  The ideas are good, the execution was awful though.

Had a terrible experience there last night. My friend ended up in the ER because they did not tell us there is peanut butter in the Barbacoa tacos. Nothing listed on the menu, the waiter didn't inquire about allergies. The manager, Jason, was very very rude and threatening to us. All he cared about is not getting sued, and not making it right with us. They didn't even comp the tacos at the end.

I've been to Brickside a few times, generally uneventful. Pretty standard bar food, generally speaking, but the experience we had the other night made me vow to never return here.  Our friend has a peanut allergy. Nothing on the menu is listed as containing peanuts. She ordered the Barbacoa tacos. As soon as she'd finished the first one, she realized something was wrong. She started to her mouth started to feel itchy.  She asked the waiter if there were any peanuts in the taco, somehow, (because who puts peanuts in a barbacoa taco, right?) and the waiter said "Not to my knowledge, but I'll check with the kitchen". Turns out, they use peanut butter in the preparation of the meat.  We complained to the manager (his name is Jason), concerned for the other people with allergies who may frequent Brickside. He did not apologize. They offered to call an ambulance, but that's where the niceties ended. He said, "We're following the law..." as though that was supposed to make up for the fact that our friend was breaking out into hives.  She went to the emergency room later that evening. They didn't even comp us the barbacoa tacos which caused the whole mess.  I'm guessing they're not going to want to cover the emergency room bill, either.

Do not eat here. The food was extremely low quality and poorly prepared. I ordered the salmon sandwich - the salmon (if it was even salmon, I suspect it may have been its cheaper cousin, char) was extremely fishy and clearly frozen. They covered the whole sandwich in "Brickside sauce," which was some sort of mixture of siracha and mayonnaise (which you would think would taste good, but it was not). My date's dinner of chicken and waffles was just as bad - the chicken was poor quality and greasy, while the waffles were dry.  The bar drinks I ordered were watery and bland. I give 1 star because the margarita was very good. I met a friend there on Sunday night 7/12/15, to have some drinks and get some burgers.
